<paragraph id="324D3698FF96A74413E0F90E296B9571" blockId="33.[189,1399,1706,1836]" pageId="33" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName id="F5F24D1BFF96A74413E0F90E2A959499" authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,434,1706,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFF96A74413E0F90E2A959499" box="[189,434,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="80">Amblypsilopus olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1BB557F1FF96A74412E4F90E29339499" box="[441,532,1706,1732]" pageId="33" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="F5F24D1BFF96A744118CF90E28AD9499" authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[721,906,1706,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andasibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFF96A744118CF90E28AD9499" box="[721,906,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="80">A. andasibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1BB557F1FF96A74410CDF90E28CC9499" box="[912,1003,1706,1732]" pageId="33" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in habitus. The latter differs from the new species in the fore tarsomere 4 entirely black, tarsomere 5 white. The fore tarsomeres 4–5 are entirely white in 
<taxonomicName id="F5F24D1BFF96A74412D5F94B2ACC9554" authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[392,491,1775,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0086EA8AFF96A74412D5F94B2ACC9554" box="[392,491,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="80">A. olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1BB557F1FF96A74412A9F95429749557" box="[500,595,1776,1802]" pageId="33" pageNumber="80" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; the long lobe of the cercus ends with one long and one short thick setae, but no long setae at middle.
</paragraph>
